<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="2" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/8835</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador on Special Mission</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_RERDI1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reading</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 588</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918</hi>.</date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 1</hi>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour, under instructions
                            from His Majesty’s Principal Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs, to
                            inform you that at the request of the Admiralty it is proposed to add to
                            the British list of absolute contraband the following: “Citric acid and
                            citrates.” Before taking this step I am instructed to enquire whether
                            your Government will be willing to take similar action. I should
                            accordingly be grateful if I might expect a reply at your early
                            convenience.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_RERDI1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Reading</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>